	<fdd:sustainabilityFactors>
		<fdd:disclosure>
			Fully documented.  Developed by Electronic Arts.
		</fdd:disclosure>
		<fdd:documentation>
			EA IFF documentation is provided online by various <a href="https://www.martinreddy.net/gfx/2d/IFF.txt">third parties</a>.
		</fdd:documentation>
		<fdd:adoption>
			<p>The <a href="https://wiki.amigaos.net/wiki/IFF_FORM_and_Chunk_Registry">IFF FORM and Chunk Registry</a> lists known chunks used by organizations and/or applications.</p>
			<p>See also <fddLink id="fdd000005">AIFF</fddLink>.
			</p>
		</fdd:adoption>
		<fdd:licensingAndPatents>
			None.
		</fdd:licensingAndPatents>
		<fdd:transparency>
			Transparent wrapper. Transparency of bitstreams within subtypes varies;         for example, see <fddLink id="fdd000011">LCPM</fddLink> and <fddLink id="fdd000230">DSD</fddLink>.
		</fdd:transparency>
		<fdd:selfDocumentation>
			The format includes headers and identifiers associated with various &#34;chunks,&#34; as the elements within the file are called.  These headers contain encoded information (as specified) used to characterize the chunk's role and characteristics.
		</fdd:selfDocumentation>
