	<fdd:notes>
		<fdd:history>
			<p>The format was brought to completion in 1985 by the electronic gaming company <a href="https://www.ea.com/">Electronic Arts</a>; some of the information about IFF refers to the Commodore-Amiga computer company and three Commodore-Amiga staff members are listed as co-authors of a key piece of documentation.  An outline of the history of Electronic Arts is provided by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electronic_Arts">Wikipedia</a>.
			</p>
			<p>The IFF format was influential and is cited as the source of ideas and approach by the creators of other tagged formats, e.g., <fddLink id="fdd000025">RIFF</fddLink> and <fddLink id="fdd000119">SMF</fddLink>.
			</p>
		</fdd:history>
	</fdd:notes>
